<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Cistus</i> spp., <i>Cotoneaster</i> spp., <i>Cytisus</i> <i>scoparius</i>, <i>Erica</i> spp., <i>Genista</i> <i>monspessulana</i>, <i>Hypericum</i> <i>canariense</i>, <i>Spartium</i> <i>junceum</i>, <i>Ulex</i> <i>europaeus</i> or other broom species are dominant in the shrub canopy. Emergent trees may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 5 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Genista monspessulana</i> or other <i>Genista</i> sp. > 15% absolute cover and > 60% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Evens and Kentner 2006).</li>
		
		<li><i>Spartium junceum</i> is > 15% absolute cover and > 60% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cistus </i>spp., <i>Cotoneaster</i> spp.,<i> Cytisus scoparius, Genista monspessulana, Hypericum canariense, Ulex europaeus</i>, or other broom species/hybrids > 50% relative cover in the shrub overstory (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Roadsides, disturbed places, eroding slopes, riverbanks, disturbed grasslands, shrublands, forest openings.  </div>
</div>

        
